  section.instruction-block
      h3.fa.fa-code
        i Setup Buttons

      ol.steps
        li
          a(class="download button button-rounded button-flat-primary button-tiny" href="#")
            i.fa.fa-download Download Buttons a  and add files to your website.

        li  Add css in the head of your webpage.
          pre class="prettyprint linenums" &lt;link href=&quot;//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.2.0/css/font-awesome.css&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot;&gt;
            &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;css/buttons.css&quot;&gt;

            &lt;script src=&quot;http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.10.1.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
            &lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;js/buttons.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

          em * You only need the font-awesome css if you're using icons
          br
          em * You only need jquery &amp; buttons.js if you're using dropdown buttons
        li Create buttons in your html.


  section.instruction-block
      h3
        i.fa.fa-github  Customize Buttons
      ol.steps
          li
            a(class="button button-rounded button-flat-action button-tiny" href="https://github.com/unicorn-ui/Buttons/")
             i.fa.fa-github Fork or Download a  the Buttons project on github.
          li Make sure you have <a target="_blank" href="http://sass-lang.com/download.html"> Sass</a>  and <a target="_blank" href="http://compass-style.org/install/"> Compass</a>  installed.
          li Edit the _options.scss with your own custom values
          li In the root of the Buttons directory type strong compass watch strong  on the command line.
          li The buttons.css file should now be updated


